{{Quote|This is the finest group of seers I've ever had before me! Raana Tey, Xamar, Q'Anilia--easily the best of their species! And who ever heard of a Feeorin Jedi? But Feln is a natural. It's the group I've foreseen. The ones who'll do what must be done!|[[Krynda Draay]]|<ref name="Knights of the Old Republic 9">[[Knights of the Old Republic 9|''Knights of the Old Republic'' 9]]</ref>}}
The '''First WatchCircle''' was a group composed of [[Jedi Seer]]s within the [[Jedi Covenant]]. It consisted of five [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Masters]], all of whom were dedicated to prevent the return of the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]].

==History==
===Formation===
The WatchCircle was selected from a group of students trained at the [[Draay Estate]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]; [[Feln]], [[Q'Anilia]], [[Raana Tey]] and [[Xamar]] were decidedly the most potent seers of all of the students Krynda Draay had trained. Her own son, [[Lucien Draay|Lucien]], was the ''Hand'', a position that was suggested by [[Haazen]], Krynda's retainer. He was responsible for handling travel arrangements, protection, etc. After being [[Knighting Ceremony/Legends|knighted]], these five [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] were often grouped together at the same postings. This was done in no small part due to the Covenant's machinations so the four [[Jedi Consular|Seers]] of the group could work closely together.

Although the Covenant was a secret society that acted separately from the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi High Council]]; the First WatchCircle's members were in the Order, and did have to answer to the newly formed Council if they wished to maintain their secrecy. All the while, they would teach their students that it is the Jedi's duty to prevent the return of the Sith.

===Assignment on Taris===
[[File:WhatTheHeck.jpg|thumb|left|200px|The [[Padawan Massacre]].]]
The group was positioned on [[Taris/Legends|Taris]] during the [[Mandalorian Wars]] at the [[Jedi Tower]] there. The Jedi High Council assigned them [[Padawan/Legends|Padawans]], much to the displeasure of the five masters who agreed they needed to be focused on their assignment of locating the [[Muur Talisman]], an ancient artifact located somewhere on Taris.

While meditating on the [[Rogue Moon]], the four seers had a [[Rogue Moon Prophecy|vision]] of the return of the Sith and the ruin of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]]. Believing that one of their Padawans would become the Sith from their visions, they decided to eliminate the threat by [[Padawan Massacre|murdering]] their Padawans at their knighting ceremony. However, due to the tardiness of Lucien's Padawan, Zayne Carrick, the plot did not go completely as planned. Q'Anilia's Padawan [[Shad Jelavan]] began to question the Masters on why Zayne would be knighted, forcing them to execute the four student present. Zayne arrived at just that moment and was able to escape. Blaming Carrick publicly as the murderer, the WatchCircle placed a bounty on the surviving Padawan. After repeated attempts (and failures) to capture Carrick, the High Council recalled the five to Coruscant in an attempt to maintain control of the situation.

===Separation anxiety===
{{Quote|You are all being reassigned-- to '''separate postings'''.|[[Vrook Lamar]]|<ref name="Knights of the Old Republic 9" />}}
[[File:Zaynelucienbind.jpg|thumb|150px|Lucien and Zayne are reunited.]]
Upon meeting with the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi High Council]], the Masters were quickly admonished for their lack of aptitude in not only training their Padawans responsibly and well, but for not sensing the darkness in Zayne. When Master Lucien requested that he and his fellow Masters be allowed to spearhead the search for his former Padawan, Master [[Vrook Lamar]] adamantly gave orders to the contrary.

Master Vrook had grown suspicious of the group over time, not knowing their true allegiance. He had come to find it strange that, regardless of where they were, these five Masters kept ending up together. Resolving this matter, Master Vrook inadvertently dissolved the First WatchCircle when he reassigned each of the five Masters to different postings around [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]].

Although separated, the five masters maintained contact. With Raana Tey on assignment to the Chancellor, Q'Anilia working to aid refugees from the War, and Lucien aiding Haazen and the Covenant, the group was growing greatly ineffective. Raana began to have a relapse of terrible nightmares, rendering her useless as a seer.

Believing Zayne was dead after the [[Courageous (Inexpugnable-class)|''Courageous'']]{{'s}} destruction, Draay was informed by Haazen that [[Arkoh Adasca]], now the owner of [[The Adasca BioMechanical Corporation of Arkania|Adascorp]], was behind a sinister plot. Lucien was ordered to investigate the situation and discover the source of the dark power. Meeting with Arkoh on board his flagship, the ''[[Arkanian Legacy]]'', Arkoh drugged Lucien, placing him in a coma. Finding himself locked up with his thought-to-be-dead Padawan, Zayne Carrick, the two were forced to work together to escape; though Lucien attempted to kill Carrick, he was forced to flee before he succeeded.

[[File:Raana_throws_Zayne.jpg|thumb|left|150px|Raana Tey [[Mission to the Jedi Tower|duels]] with Carrick moments before her death.]]
On Taris, the Mandalorians, led by [[Cassus Fett]], had already [[Taris Siege|besieged]] the planet. Raana Tey managed to locate the missing senator [[Haydel Goravvus]] who was leading the [[Taris Resistance]]. Tey manipulated [[Shel Jelavan]], sister of deceased Padawan Shad Jelavan, ordering her to find Carrick and to extract revenge on him for murdering her brother. After being betrayed by Shel at the Jedi Tower, Raana attempted to stop Zayne from escaping by leaping onto the roof where she was greatly injured. The tower was destroyed, along with Raana herself when [[Marn Hierogryph]] detonated explosives at the base.

While holding Raana's funeral on Coruscant, the remaining seers of the WatchCircle had a vision involving the [[Muur Talisman]], and intelligent [[rakghoul]]s who could use weapons and ships. According to Zayne and [[Skywalker family/Legends|three others]], [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|one dark armored]], a [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|calm one]] and a [[Cade Skywalker|pirate]], everything is happening now. Concluding that if Zayne would sink even deeper into the dark side if he found the Talisman, Lucien sent [[Covenant Shadow]] [[Celeste Morne]] to recover the Talisman.

Haazen later used his resources to put Lucien on the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi High Council]] in order for the Shadows to move about freely. After his appointment, Haazen tells Lucien that Morne had arrived at [[Odryn]]. Feln went back to his home planet where the Covenant was secretly testing [[Sith artifact/Legends|Sith artifacts]] to meet up with Celeste, only to find Zayne and Gryph captured by the [[Feeorin/Legends|Feeorins]]. Suspecting that Zayne killed Celeste and was further corrupted by the Talisman, Lucien ordered [[Option Ossus]], which would destroy the [[Sanctum of the Exalted]]. However, Haazen interjected, not wanting to lose such a valuable station. After a holographic argument, Feln decided to pummel Zayne into pulp. But when Zayne's allies returned to pick him up, Feln misinterpreted it as a raid and destroyed the Sanctum. However, this also destroyed the village below, angering the villagers, who butchered Feln, resulting in his part in the Rogue Moon Prophecy being fulfilled.

===The breaking of the Circle===
After Feln's death, Lucien had Master Xamar assigned to the [[Republic Navy/Legends|Republic Navy]]. Xamar complied reluctantly, having remembered that in his part of the Rogue Moon Prophecy, he was killed by friendly fire from Republic ships. However, Xamar begun to have doubts about what the WatchCircle had done, and after capturing Zayne Carrick and Marn Hierogryph on Coruscant, he confessed to the Council what he and his fellow Covenant members had done, in the hope of absolving Krynda, whom he remained loyal to. Xamar proceeded to accompany Zayne, who was disguised as a Sith, to the Draay estate to draw Krynda out into the open and subsequently rescue her. Unfortunately, Haazen saw through this plot and revealed himself as a servant of the dark side. This proved fatal to Master Xamar, who was killed when a fleet under Haazen's command, having sliced the [[Vanjervalis Chain]], fired on the Draay Estate. He then revealed that Zayen, Gryph, Lucien, Q'Anilia and Haazen himself were the figures in Krynda's [[Prophecy of the Five]].

As chaos ensued at the Estate, Q'Anilia rushed to find Krynda. Upon finding what she assumed to be her Lady's dead body, the Miraluka poisoned herself, ending her life. With the Draay Estate in ruins and all members but Lucien dead, the WatchCircle was no more.

